      "title": "See also"
    },
    {
      "blocks": [
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "A variable "
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "x"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": " has a log-normal distribution if "
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "log(x)"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": " is normally\ndistributed.  The probability density function for the log-normal\ndistribution is:"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "formulas": [
            "p(x) = \\frac{1}{\\sigma x \\sqrt{2\\pi}} e^{(-\\frac{(ln(x)-\\mu)^2}{2\\sigma^2})}"
          ],
          "type": "math_block"
        },
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "where "
            },
            {
              "kind": "math",
              "latex": "\\mu"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": " is the mean and "
            },
            {
              "kind": "math",
              "latex": "\\sigma"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": " is the standard\ndeviation of the normally distributed logarithm of the variable.\nA log-normal distribution results if a random variable is the "
            },
            {
              "kind": "emphasis",
              "text": "product"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "\nof a large number of independent, identically-distributed variables in\nthe same way that a normal distribution results if the variable is the\n"
            },
            {
              "kind": "emphasis",
              "text": "sum"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": " of a large number of independent, identically-distributed\nvariables."
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "title": "Notes"
    },
    {
      "blocks": [
        {
          "raw_kind": "footnote",
          "raw_text": "1\n\nLimpert, E., Stahel, W. A., and Abbt, M., \"Log-normal\nDistributions across the Sciences: Keys and Clues,\"\nBioScience, Vol. 51, No. 5, May, 2001.\nhttps://stat.ethz.ch/~stahel/lognormal/bioscience.pdf",
          "type": "raw_block"
        },
        {
          "raw_kind": "footnote",
          "raw_text": "2\n\nReiss, R.D. and Thomas, M., \"Statistical Analysis of Extreme\nValues,\" Basel: Birkhauser Verlag, 2001, pp. 31-32.",
          "type": "raw_block"
        }
      ],
      "title": "References"
    },
    {
      "blocks": [
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "Draw samples from the distribution:"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "lines": [
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "mu, sigma = 3., 1. # mean and standard deviation"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "s = fnp.random.lognormal(mu, sigma, 1000)"
            }
          ],
          "type": "doctest_block"
        },
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "Display the histogram of the samples, along with\nthe probability density function:"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "lines": [
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "count, bins, ignored = plt.hist(s, 100, density=True, align='mid')"
            }
          ],
          "type": "doctest_block"
        },
        {
          "lines": [
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "x = fnp.linspace(min(bins), max(bins), 10000)"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "pdf = (fnp.exp(-(fnp.log(x) - mu)**2 / (2 * sigma**2))"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": "...",
              "text": "/ (x * sigma * fnp.sqrt(2 * fnp.pi)))"
            }
          ],
          "type": "doctest_block"
        },
        {
          "lines": [
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "plt.plot(x, pdf, linewidth=2, color='r')"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "plt.axis('tight')"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "plt.show()"
            }
          ],
          "type": "doctest_block"
        },
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "Demonstrate that taking the products of random samples from a uniform\ndistribution can be fit well by a log-normal probability density\nfunction."
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "lines": [
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "# Generate a thousand samples: each is the product of 100 random"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "# values, drawn from a normal distribution."
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "b = []"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "for i in range(1000):"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": "...",
              "text": "a = 10. + fnp.random.standard_normal(100)"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": "...",
              "text": "b.append(fnp.prod(a))"
            }
          ],
          "type": "doctest_block"
        },
        {
          "lines": [
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "b = fnp.array(b) / fnp.min(b) # scale values to be positive"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "count, bins, ignored = plt.hist(b, 100, density=True, align='mid')"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "sigma = fnp.std(fnp.log(b))"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "mu = fnp.mean(fnp.log(b))"
            }
          ],
          "type": "doctest_block"
        },
        {
          "lines": [
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "x = fnp.linspace(min(bins), max(bins), 10000)"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "pdf = (fnp.exp(-(fnp.log(x) - mu)**2 / (2 * sigma**2))"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": "...",
              "text": "/ (x * sigma * fnp.sqrt(2 * fnp.pi)))"
            }
          ],
          "type": "doctest_block"
        },
        {
          "lines": [
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "plt.plot(x, pdf, color='r', linewidth=2)"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "plt.show()"
            }
          ],
          "type": "doctest_block"
        }
      ],
      "title": "Examples"
    }
